Lopez released her first single with Island Records, "[[On the Floor]]", featuring Pitbull. The song topped the charts across the globe; peaking at number three on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], her highest peaking song on that chart in over eight years. The song became one of the most successful singles of the year.<ref name="Digital report 2012">{{cite web|title=IFPI digital music report 2012 – key facts and figures |url=http://ifpi.com/content/library/DMR2012_key_facts_and_figures.pdf|publisher=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|accessdate=2012-01-23}}</ref> ''Love?'' was finally released on May 3, 2011 in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|last=Shetler|first=Scott|title=Jennifer Lopez, 'Love?' – Album Review|url=http://popcrush.com/jennifer-lopez-love-album-review/|publisher=PopCrush|accessdate=2011-05-04}}</ref> The album was a moderate commercial success, and viewed as a humble comeback from Lopez, as many had considered her recording career over.<ref name=lovereview /> ''Love?'' produced two more singles: "[[I'm Into You]]" featuring [[Lil Wayne]] and "[[Papi (song)|Papi]]", which became her tenth and eleventh chart-toppers on the ''Billboard'' Hot Dance Club Songs chart.<ref name=Imintoyou>{{cite web|title=I'm Into You – Jennifer Lopez (Billboard)|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/jennifer-lopez-featuring-lil-wayne/i-m-into-you/25408370|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] (billboard.com)|accessdate=2012-01-29}}</ref> In July, Lopez launched Love and Light, a flanker fragrance to Love and Glamour, exclusively on HSN. According to Lopez, the woody, floral scent is "less about the world around you" and "more about your inner light". She concluded by stating that: "It's about how you feel inside, it's not about your outside world".<ref>{{cite web  |url=http://news.instyle.com/2011/07/01/jennifer-lopez-hsn-love-and-light |title=Jennifer Lopez — HSN — Love and Light : InStyle.com What's Right Now |publisher=News.instyle.com |date=July 1, 2011 |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref> 51,000 bottles of the fragrance were sold at its premiere, becoming Lopez's most successful fragrance launch to date, making over $2.9 million.<ref>{{cite web  |url=http://news.instyle.com/2011/07/07/jennifer-lopez-hsn-love-and-light-sales |title=Jennifer Lopez HSN — Love & Light : InStyle.com What's Right Now |publisher=News.instyle.com |date=July 7, 2011 |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref> On July 15, following seven years of marriage, Lopez and Anthony's representatives announced that the couple were separating.<ref name=splitting>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebritynews/news/jennifer-lopez-and-marc-anthony-split-2011157 |title=Jennifer Lopez and Marc Anthony Split |publisher=UsMagazine.com |accessdate=2011-08-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lopez and Anthony Split|url=http://www.moono.com/news/news17145.html|publisher=(moono.com)|accessdate=2012-02-02|date=July 15, 2011}}</ref> In September, Lopez and Anthony launched a clothing and accessories line for [[Kohl's]] with [[Tommy Hilfiger]]. Although their designs were originally set to be a collaborative effort, following the couple's separation, Lopez solely designed the women's collection while Anthony designed the menswear.<ref name="goahead">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez – Jennifer Lopez's Fashion Line To Go Ahead|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/jennifer-lopezs-fashion-line-to-go-ahead_1233187|publisher=(contactmusic.com)|accessdate=2012-02-05|date=July 19, 2011}}</ref> Lopez's women's line includes contemporary sportswear, dresses, handbags, jewelry, shoes and sleepwear. In addition to the clothing line, she also launched the Jennifer Lopez Home Collection, featuring bedding, towels and luggage.<ref name="Lopez Previews Her Kohl's Collection">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez Previews Her Kohl's Collection|url=http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2011/08/12/jennifer-lopez-for-kohls|publisher=(stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com)|accessdate=2012-01-31|date=August 12, 2011}}</ref> Later that same month [[Fiat]], an Italian automobile manufacturer, enlisted Lopez to promote their products, including the [[Fiat 500 (2007)|2012 Fiat 500 Cabrio]]. Olivier Francois, the [[Chrysler]] chief marketing officer, said in a statement that: "Jennifer fits perfectly with the brand not because of who she is but because of what she is — authentic, passionate, modern and a fighter determined to stand out from the rest".<ref>{{cite web|last=Lienert |first=Anita |url=http://www.insideline.com/fiat/500/2012/fiat-and-jennifer-lopez-hook-up.html |title=Fiat and Jennifer Lopez Hook Up |publisher=Insideline.com |date=September 13, 2011 |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref> Controversy arose for one of her commercials for Fiat, "My World", that depicts Lopez leaving Manhattan and driving through The Bronx neighborhood where she grew up. It was reported that Lopez did not return to The Bronx to shoot the commercial, but instead filmed her close-up shots in Los Angeles, while a body double was used for the car scenes through The Bronx.<ref name="Lopez Fakes Fiat Commercial">{{cite web|author=Jennifer Lopez |url=http://eonline.com/news/car_trouble_jennifer_lopez_fakes_fiat/276684 |title=Car Trouble? Jennifer Lopez Fakes Fiat Commercial With Help From Bronx Body Double |publisher=[[E! Online]]. [[E!]] |date=November 23, 2011 |accessdate=2012-06-10}}</ref><ref name="Lopez Asked to Renounce Fiat">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/01/12/jennifer-lopez-uani-fiat-iran-terrorism-endorsement-renounce-ties_n_1202441.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Asked To Renounce Fiat Relationship Due To Terrorist Ties |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref>

=== 2012: Dance Again World Tour and eighth studio album ===
[[File:Jennifer Lopez - Pop Music Festival (32).jpg|thumb|left|Lopez performing "Goin' In" during the Pop Music Festival in São Paulo, Brazil]]

In January 2012, Lopez returned as judge on the [[American Idol (season 11)|eleventh season]] of ''American Idol'', earning a reported $20 million.<ref name="Forbes2">{{cite news|author=Hannah Elliott |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/hannahelliott/2012/05/16/the-real-american-idol-how-j-lo-got-her-mojo-back/ |title=The Real American Idol: How J.Lo Got Her Mojo Back |publisher=Forbes |date=April 18, 2012 |accessdate=2012-05-24}}</ref> The season was not as successful as its previous ten seasons and for the first time in the show's history, it was not the most-watched primetime television show.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/full-2011-2012-tv-season-series-rankings/ |title=Full 2011–2012 TV Season Series Rankings |publisher=Deadline.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-10}}</ref> Later that same month a new talent show, ''[[Q'Viva! The Chosen|¡Q'Viva! The Chosen]]'', created by [[Simon Fuller]] premiered on [[Univision]] and was a hit for the channel.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sheridan|first=Emily|title='Sometimes you don't agree and I say be quiet': Jennifer Lopez admits it can be difficult working with estranged husband Marc Anthony|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2094297/Jennifer-Lopez-admits-difficult-working-estranged-husband-Marc-Anthony.html|work=Daily Mail |publisher=(dailymail.co.uk)|accessdate=2012-02-12|date=January 31, 2012|location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennifer-lopez-marc-anthonys-qviva-250584 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | title=Jennifer Lopez and Marc Anthony's 'Q'Viva: The Chosen': First Broadcast Partners Announced | date=October 19, 2011}}</ref> It followed Lopez, Anthony and director-choeographer [[Jamie King]] as they travelled across 21 countries in Latin America to find new talent for a [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] show. On May 18, Lopez returned to the big screen co-starring alongside an [[ensemble cast]] consisting of [[Cameron Diaz]], [[Elizabeth Banks]], [[Matthew Morrison]] and [[Dennis Quaid]] in the film ''[[What to Expect When You're Expecting (film)|What to Expect When You're Expecting]]''.<ref name="Lopez">{{cite news|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2011/06/24/jennifer-lopez-what-to-expect-when-youre-expecting|title=Jennifer Lopez signs on for 'What to Expect When You're Expecting'|last=Labrecque|first=Jeff|work=Entertainment Weekly|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=June 24, 2011|accessdate=2011-07-23<!--archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/60O53uOVo |archivedate=2011-07-23 -->}}</ref> Based on the [[What to Expect When You're Expecting|book of the same name]], Lopez plays Holly, a woman who adopts a baby from abroad with her husband after difficulty conceiving. With a budget of $40 million, the film grossed a total of $74 million worldwide, becoming a moderate commerical success.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=whattoexpect.htm |title=What to Expect When You're Expecting (2012) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=May 27, 2012 |accessdate=2012-07-10}}</ref> The film, however, received generally negative reviews from film critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/what_to_expect_when_youre_expecting |title=What to Expect When You're Expecting |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |date= |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref> In late May, Lopez released her fragrance [[Glowing (fragrance)|Glowing]], which she described as an "evolution" of Glow by J.Lo.<ref name="Huffington">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/10/glowing-jennifer-lopez-launching-new-fragrance_n_1268972.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Launches 'Glowing' Perfume With Naked Ad, Light-Up Bottle (PHOTOS) |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Palomares |first=Sugey |url=http://www.latina.com/beauty/skin-nails/jlo-says-new-perfume-glowing-step-beyond-glow |title=J.Lo Says New Perfume 'Glowing' Is "A Step Beyond Glow" |publisher=Latina |date= |accessdate=2012-03-03}}</ref>

In early June, Lopez released "[[Goin' In]]", a song that promoted the dance film ''[[Step Up Revolution]]'' (2012).<ref>{{cite web|author=Robbie Daw |url=http://idolator.com/6519871/j-lo-flo-rida-goin-in |title=Jennifer Lopez & Flo Rida Are "Goin' In": Hear The New Song &#124; Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on |publisher=Idolator.com |date=May 24, 2012 |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref> On June 14, Lopez launched the [[Dance Again World Tour]], her first headlining concert tour. The tour began in Panama and traveled across Latin America, ending in Brazil on July 1.<ref name="My Diary May 3">{{cite web |url=http://jenniferlopez.com/blog/post/my-diary|title=My Diary |author= |date=3 May 2012 |work=Jennifer Lopez Website |publisher= |accessdate=2012-05-13|archiveurl=http://www.freezepage.com/1336988633AFEXHXNLRN |archivedate=2012-05-13}}</ref> Later that same month, Lopez launched [[Teeology]], a Los Angeles-based luxury [[T-shirt]] [[e-commerce]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Andrea Huspeni |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/jennifer-lopez-to-launch-teeology-2012-7 |title=Jennifer Lopez to Launch Teeology |publisher=Business Insider |date=July 12, 2012 |accessdate=2012-08-05}}</ref> Lopez voiced Shira, a saber tooth tiger, in the animated film, ''[[Ice Age: Continental Drift]]'', the fourth film in the ''[[Ice Age (franchise)|Ice Age]]'' franchise.<ref name="Rovi Ice Age 4">{{cite web|first=Jeremy |last=Wheeler |url=http://www.allrovi.com/movies/movie/ice-age-continental-drift-3d-v516738 |title=Ice Age: Continental Drift 3D – Cast, Reviews, Summary, and Awards |work=AllRovi |publisher=Rovi Corporation |accessdate=2011-10-30}}</ref> The film debuted at number one at the US Box Office, having grossed $46 million in its opening weekend, becoming Lopez's highest opening weekend figure.<ref>{{cite news|author=Associated Press|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2174019/Ice-Age-4-Continental-Drift-movie-tops-box-office-46m-opening-weekend.html|title=Ice Age movie tops box office with $46 million opening weekend...but Batman is lurking to snatch the title|date=15 July 2012|publisher=''[[Daily Mail]]''|accessdate=2012-07-24}}</ref> With a $95 million production budget, the film has since grossed $867 million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=iceage4.htm |title=Ice Age: Continental Drift (2012) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=July 13, 2012 |accessdate=2012-11-1}}</ref> On July 14, Lopez launched her [[Enrique Iglesias & Jennifer Lopez Tour|co-headlining concert tour]] with Spanish recording artist [[Enrique Iglesias]]. The tour, an extension of the Dance Again World Tour, traveled across nineteen North American cities during the months of July, August and September.<ref>{{cite web|author=Becky Bain |url=http://idolator.com/6415311/jennifer-lopez-enrique-iglesias-2012-summer-tour-dates |title=Jennifer Lopez And Enrique Iglesias Reveal 2012 North American Tour Dates &#124; Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on |publisher=Idolator.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref>

Lopez's first greatest hits album, ''[[Dance Again... the Hits]]'', was released on July 24, 2012 in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|author=Published Tuesday, Jun 19 2012, 11:53am EDT |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a388349/jennifer-lopez-to-release-dance-again-the-hits-next-month.html |title=Jennifer Lopez to release 'Dance Again: The Hits' next month? |publisher=Digital Spy |date=June 19, 2012 |accessdate=2012-07-10}}</ref> The album was released by Epic Records, as Lopez owed them one final album to end her contract, despite previously announcing in 2010 that she had fulfilled her contract with the label.<ref name="radio1">{{cite web|url=http://925maxima.radio.com/2012/05/28/jennifer-lopez-interview-new-single-goin-in |title=Jennifer Lopez Talks About Her New Single "Goin' In" |publisher=925maxima.radio.com |date=May 28, 2012 |accessdate=2012-06-23}}</ref> It was preceded by the release of its sole single, "[[Dance Again]]", in April. Lopez, at the time of the single's release, was unsure if it would be the lead single from a greatest hits album or her eighth studio album.<ref name="ryaninterview">{{cite web|url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2012/03/30/jennifer-lopez-talks-dance-again-her-upcoming-album-audio/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Talks 'Dance Again' & Her Upcoming 'Greatest Hits' Album [AUDIO&#93; &#124; Ryan Seacrest – The official entertainment news site of American Idol host and American Top 40 on air radio personality! |publisher=Ryan Seacrest |date= |accessdate=2012-03-31}}</ref> The song was a moderate commercial success, peaking within the top ten in almost all of the countries where it was released. "Dance Again" and "Goin' In" both reached the top of the ''Billboard'' Hot Dance Club Songs, giving Lopez her twelfth and thirteenth number one on that chart, respectively. Additionally, "Goin' In" became her tenth consecutive number one on the chart, tying [[Katy Perry]] for having the most consecutive numbers one on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/news#/column/chartbeat/chart-highlights-gotye-extends-multi-format-1007763752.story |title=Latest Music News, Band, Artist, Musician & Music Video News |publisher=Billboard.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-08}}</ref> In September, [[nuvoTV]], a small English-language network aimed at Latino viewers, announced plans for a "marketing and programming partnership" with Lopez that will make her a part-owner of the channel. Lopez will produce programming for the network through her production company, [[Nuyorican Productions]] and will appear occasionally on-air. She will also act as a promotional ambassador for the network.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/television/news/story/2012-09-11/jennifer-lopez-nuvo-tv/57750774/1 |title=Jennifer Lopez joins Hispanic TV network Nuvo – |publisher=Usatoday.com |date=September 11, 2012 |accessdate=2012-10-03}}</ref> In November, RedOne revealed that he is the executive producer of Lopez's upcoming eighth studio album. He told [[MTV News]] of the album: "It's just amazing. It's mixed [styles]. It's everything about Jennifer Lopez". He elaborated by stating: "It's not one thing; it's everything you experience. It's a very special album. It feels like this album, to us, has to have everything about her, not just one thing. You're going to have all the sides, kind of urban/hip-hop and the commercial, like the way she did with Ja Rule. It's everything you love about her [including] the dance, the rhythmic, the Latin".<ref>http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1696687/j-lo-jennifer-hudson-red-one.jhtml</ref>

== Artistry ==

=== Musical style ===
{{Further|List of songs recorded by Jennifer Lopez}}
<!-- PLEASE DO NOT ADD OR REMOVE ANY OF THE SAMPLES BELOW WITHOUT FIRST DISCUSSING IT ON THE TALK PAGE. -->
