<!-- PLEASE DO NOT ADD OR REMOVE ANY OF THE SAMPLES ABOVE WITHOUT FIRST DISCUSSING IT ON THE TALK PAGE. -->

Over the course of her musical career, Lopez's music and the genre which it has been perceived as, has ranged from [[Pop music|pop]] and [[Latin pop]],<ref name="Jennifer Lopez's Flight to Fame">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez's Flight to Fame: From Television to Music and Back|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/jennifer-lopezs-flight-fame-television-to-7950048.html?cat=37|publisher=(voices.yahoo.com)}}</ref> to [[dance music|dance]], [[Funk music|funk]] and [[contemporary R&B|R&B]].<ref name="Jennifer Lopez Favours Women On American Idol">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez – Jennifer Lopez Favours Women On American Idol|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/jennifer-lopez-favours-women-on-american-idol_1212584|publisher=(contactmusic.com)|accessdate=2012-02-12|date=April 14, 2011}}</ref> ''On the 6'' saw Lopez work with producers [[Rodney Jerkins]], [[Sean Combs|P. Diddy]], [[Emilio Estefan]] and [[Ric Wake]], while collaborating with rappers [[Big Pun]] and [[Fat Joe]] and [[Marc Anthony]].<ref name="On the 6 booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=On the 6 |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=1999 |format=Booklet |publisher=[[Work Records]], a division of [[Sony Music Entertainment]] |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> The album showcases Lopez's "sultry, versatile" voice in a "number of settings", including pop ballads, Latin pop and R&B. The wide array of producers make a "perfectly polished and varied album", with a musical blend that Lopez calls "Latin soul". Smooth ballads such as "Could This Be Love" and "[[No Me Ames]]", a duet with Anthony, dominate the first half of the album; showing off the "gentler side" of Lopez's voice. Along with the album's first single, "If You Had My Love", "Feelin' So Good" and "Let's Get Loud" contain a fiery, soulful sound that is in "Lopez's public persona". The second half of ''On the 6'' capitalizes on Lopez's "spicy, upbeat side", as heard on "Waiting for Tonight" and "Open Off My Love", which draws inspiration from rap, R&B and Latin styles with its arrangement of horns, keyboards and beats.<ref name="Allmusic On the 6">{{cite web|last=Phares |first=Heather |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/on-the-6-r417448 |title=On the 6 – Jennifer Lopez |work=AllMusic|publisher= Rovi Corporation |accessdate=2011-11-10}}</ref> ''J.Lo'' saw Lopez collaborating with the same people that she had worked with on ''On the 6'', with some critics citing the two to be essentially "the same album".<ref name="Allmusic J.Lo">{{cite web|last=Thomas |first=Stephen |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/j-lo-mw0000103727 |title=J. Lo – Jennifer Lopez : Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |publisher=AllMusic |date=January 23, 2001 |accessdate=2012-08-18}}</ref><ref name="J.Lo booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=J.Lo |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2001 |format=Booklet |publisher=[[Epic Records]], a division of [[Sony Music Entertainment]] |location=New York City, NY}}</ref>

Lopez's musical style saw a change with the release of ''This Is Me... Then'', which saw her continue working Rooney, who produced the majority of the album.<ref name="This Is Me booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=This Is Me... Then |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2002 |format=Booklet |publisher=[[Epic Records]], a division of [[Sony Music Entertainment]] |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> The music was described as having a mature [[contemporary R&B]] sound that was not present in her previous work. The album, which has been described as more unified than its predecessors, is ripe with live instrumentation and stripped of the Latin pop songs that "never seemed quite authentic". ''This Is Me... Then'' contains a mix of "the old with the new": Lopez and [[LL Cool J]] interpolate Debra and Ronnie Laws' "Very Special" on "[[All I Have (song)|All I Have]]", while "Jenny from the Block" is structured around several samples, including the Beatnuts' 1999 hit "Watch Out Now", Herbie Mann's "Hijack" and KRS-One's "South Bronx". On ''This Is Me... Then'', Lopez makes references to her boyfriends of the past and present, as heard in "Still" and the vintage-sounding "[[Baby I Love U!]]", respectively. "Dear Ben", an ode to Affleck, has been described as the album's "glowing centerpiece", in which Lopez sings: "I love you / You're perfect / A manifestation of my dreams".<ref name="Slant This Is Me">{{cite web|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/jennifer-lopez-this-is-me-then/251 |title=Jennifer Lopez: This Is Me...Then &#124; Music Review |publisher=Slant Magazine |date=November 20, 2002 |accessdate=2012-01-23}}</ref> For ''Rebirth'' Lopez re-teamed up with frequent collaborators Jerkins and Rooney and also worked with new producers, such as [[Big Boi]] and [[Timbaland]].<ref name="Rebirth booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=Rebirth |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2005 |format=Booklet |publisher=[[Epic Records]], a division of [[Sony Music Entertainment]] |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> It is a "straight-ahead" dance album, that alternates between "sweet, breezy pop" tunes, such as "Still Around", and "hard-driving" club tracks, such as "Cherry Pie".<ref name="Allmusic Rebirth">{{cite web|last=Thomas |first=Stephen |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/rebirth-mw0000142788 |title=Rebirth – Jennifer Lopez : Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |publisher=AllMusic |date=March 1, 2005 |accessdate=2012-08-18}}</ref>

''Como Ama una Mujer'' was produced by husband Anthony, with additional production from Estéfano and Julio Reyes.<ref name="Como booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=Como ama una mujer |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2007 |format=Booklet |publisher=[[Epic Records]], a division of [[Sony Music Entertainment]] |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> For ''Brave'', Lopez collaborated solely with producers she had not previously worked with, including [[J. R. Rotem]] and [[Ryan Tedder]], as well as production teams [[Bloodshy & Avant]], [[The Clutch]] and [[Lynn & Wade LLP]].<ref name="Brave booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=Brave |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2007 |format=Booklet |publisher=Epic Records, a division of Sony Music Entertainment |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> The album's opening track, "Stay Together", is an anthem of [[monogamy]] where she declares that heartbreak and dating are overrated and that "toughing it out is the new trend". The rest of the record plays off that theme, "as nights out on the town are traded for cozy nights at home". ''Brave'', a dance album, is filled with bright beats and happy hooks, that isn't meant for clubbing: "it's dance music for home, maybe background music for some chores".<ref name="Allmusic Brave">{{cite web|last=Erlewine |first=Stephen Thomas |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/brave-r1208434 |title=Brave – Jennifer Lopez |work=AllMusic|publisher= Rovi Corporation |accessdate=2011-11-10}}</ref> Her seventh album ''Love?'' saw Lopez go further in the dance music direction,<ref>{{cite news |last=Markovitz |first=Adam |title=Jennifer Lopez – Love? (album review) |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20485119,00.html |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=Ew.com / [[CNN]] |date=April 27, 2011 |accessdate=2011-05-28}}</ref> working with producers [[D'Mile]], [[RedOne]], [[Tricky Stewart]] and [[The-Dream]].<ref name="Love booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=Love? |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2011 |format=Booklet |publisher=[[Island Records]], a division of [[Universal Music Group]] |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> On the album, Lopez covers topics such as her past loves in her songs, "[[One Love (Jennifer Lopez song)|One Love]]" and "[[(What Is) Love?]]" which she goes into details through lyrics about her remaining an optimistic about love.<ref name=kidstwins />

=== Influences ===
Lopez, who has always loved a "good lyricist", has been most influenced by the "different" performers, such as [[Tina Turner]], [[James Brown]], [[Michael Jackson]] and [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]].<ref name="10 Questions for Lopez">{{cite news|author=By DEPARTMENT Thursday, Oct. 18, 2007 |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1673250,00.html |title=10 Questions for Jennifer Lopez |publisher=TIME |date=October 18, 2007 |accessdate=2012-08-18}}</ref> From a musical perspective, Lopez has viewed Madonna as her greatest influence.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez Cites Madonna As Biggest Musical Influence|url=http://popdirt.com/jennifer-lopez-cites-madonna-as-biggest-musical-influence/12652/|accessdate=2012-02-12|date=February 2, 2003}}</ref> In an interview with ''NY Rock'', when asked who was her first biggest musical influence, Lopez stated: "I think Madonna. For my era growing up, [she] was the quintessential performer, and a push-the-envelope type of person. I don't think that I'm a push-the-envelope type of person. But I think Madonna was so visionary. And in her shows, she was so expressive. So that was very inspiring for me as a young girl. I remember seeing a lot of her shows".<ref>{{cite web|last=Miller|first=Praire|title=NY Rock Interview with Jennifer Lopez|url=http://www.nyrock.com/interviews/2002/lopez_int3.asp|publisher=(nyrock.com)|accessdate=2012-02-12}}</ref> According to Fouz-Hernández, female pop performers like Lopez were like "Madonna's daughters" in the "very direct sense that they grew up listening to and admiring Madonna" and decided they wanted to "be like her".<ref>{{Cite book |last = Fouz-Hernández |first = Santiago |first2 = Freya |last2 = Jarman-Ivens |title = Madonna's Drowned Worlds |publisher = [[Ashgate Publishing|Ashgate Publishing, Ltd]] |isbn = 0-7546-3372-1 |year = 2004}}</ref> Lopez considers [[Janet Jackson]] a big influence on her dancing and music videos. She has lauded Jackson's videography, stating her music videos "had such an impact on me as a fan but also as an artist."<ref>{{cite news|last=Rodmon|first=Sarah|title=Music; Has Janet Jackson earned her diva wings?; Two FleetCenter shows are just one criterion|accessdate=2012-03-15|newspaper=[[Boston Herald]]|date=August 24, 2001}}</ref> 

Growing up, Lopez looked up to Puero Rican actress [[Rita Moreno]], stating that there were: "Zero Latinos on TV, so Rita Moreno was the only one I identified to".<ref name=rantrack /> She has named [[Barbra Streisand]] as her idol, saying that she felt that she "graduated" from music when she sang Streisand's music.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez 'graduated' as a singer while singing for hubby|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/jennifer-lopez-graduated-as-a-singer-while/558630/}}</ref> Other musical influences for Lopez include Latin performers [[Selena]] and [[Gloria Estefan]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Harrington|first=Richard|title=Jennifer Lopez, finding her voice|work=The Washington Post|date=July 14, 1999}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ankeny |first=Jason |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/jennifer-lopez-p371168 |title=Jennifer Lopez |publisher=AllMusic |accessdate=2012-03-17}}</ref> Lopez has also stated that newer artists have also more inspired her, rather than influenced her as an artist, such as American singer-songwriter [[Lady Gaga]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Dokren|first=Joanne|title=Jennifer Lopez "Motivated & Inspired" By Lady GaGa|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/jennifer-lopez/277574-jennifer-lopez-lady-gaga-love|publisher=(mtv.co.uk)|accessdate=2012-02-12|date=June 16, 2011}}</ref> After motherhood, Lopez credited her twins as an influence in the direction of her music.<ref name=kidstwins>{{cite web|last=Roberts|first=Steven|title=Jennifer Lopez Talks About Influence Of Her Twins On New Music|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1613887/jennifer-lopez-talks-about-influence-her-twins-on-new-music.jhtml|publisher=(mtv.com)|accessdate=2012-02-12|date=June 15, 2009}}</ref> According to Lopez, who has been publicly criticized for her "limited" [[soubrette]] vocal type, she has always been insecure about the strength of her voice.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/pages/jenniferlopezx18x03x05 |title=Jennifer Lopez – Rebirth – Album Review |publisher=Contactmusic.com |accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vocalous.com/jennifer-lopez-singing-voice-type.html |title=Jennifer Lopez's Voice Type (Classic Soubrette) " Jennifer Lopez Singing Voice Type – Classic Soubrette Lessons |publisher=Vocalous.com |date=June 11, 2011 |accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref><ref name=vocall>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez finds her voice on new album|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2011/02/02/jennifer-lopez-finds-her-voice-on-new-album/#more-72798|accessdate=2012-02-12}}</ref> She cited Anthony as giving her the confidence to sing. She said in an interview with ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' in 2012: "He always told me what a beautiful voice I have {{sic}} He was like, ‘It’s in there; you just gotta let it out. It’s a confidence thing with you.’ Then all of a sudden one day I was like, ‘I’m good at this!’"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popcrush.com/jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-confidence-sing/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Says Marc Anthony Gave Her Confidence to Sing |publisher=Popcrush.com |accessdate=2012-03-21}}</ref> Lopez is also greatly influenced by the culture of her hometown, [[the Bronx, New York|The Bronx]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biography.com/people/jennifer-lopez-9542231/videos/jennifer-lopez-musical-roots-2197970649 |title=Jennifer Lopez - Musical Roots - Jennifer Lopez Videos |publisher=Biography.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-20}}</ref>

=== Choreography and music videos ===
{{Further|Jennifer Lopez videography}}

[[File:Jennifer Lopez - Papi (Music Video).jpg|right|thumb|Lopez surrounded by men in her music video for "[[Papi (song)|Papi]]" during a signature dance break, which Lopez often incorporates in her music videos]]

Lopez, who is a professionally training dancer, specializing in [[ballet]], [[jazz]] and [[flamenco]], is well known for her Latin pop influenced dancing abilities.<ref>{{cite web|author=Biography |url=http://www.amillionlives.net/jennifer-lopez-biography-the-dancer-turned-popular-american-actress-fashion-designer-and-singer.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Biography – the Dancer Turned Popular American Actress, Fashion Designer and Singer &#124; amillionlives.net – Rife with Life |publisher=Amillionlives.net |accessdate=2012-03-17}}</ref><ref name=ballet>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecinemasource.com/blog/interviews/jennifer-lopez-interview-for-shall-we-dance/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Interview for Shall We Dance? |publisher=The Cinema Source |date=January 28, 2008 |accessdate=2012-03-17}}</ref> Lopez has stated that: "I feel sexiest when I'm dancing [...] I'm a dancer, so dance and choreography have always been a way to express myself. Anything you do with music or a song, or even playing a character, is a way of expressing yourself. Dance just happens to be a very sensual way of doing it".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/entertainment/post/2012/08/jennifer-lopez-expresses-herself-on-stage/1#.UDGlyt1lREM |title=Jennifer Lopez expresses herself on stage |publisher=Content.usatoday.com |date=August 18, 2012 |accessdate=2012-09-10}}</ref> She has worked with well known choreographers such as [[Dave Scott (choreographer)|Dave Scott]], Judd, [[Brian Friedman]], [[Wade Robson]], [[Tyce Diorio]], [[Travis Payne]], Jeri Slaughter, [[Laurie Ann Gibson]], [[Mia Michaels]] and [[Tina Landon]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Ditzian |first=Eric |url=http://www.mtv.ca/vma/2009/article.jhtml?id=20276 |title=Michael Jackson VMA Tribute Will Include Top Choreographers &#124; MTV.ca &#124; News |publisher=MTV.ca |date=September 13, 2009 |accessdate=2012-03-17}}</ref>

Lopez is well known for her [[Jennifer Lopez videography|music videos]], which often incorporate themes and dance breaks. The clip for Lopez's debut single "If You Had My Love" caused a stir for it's use of internet surveillance and voyeuristic themes.<ref name="aolradioblog1">{{cite web|author=<!-- surphace start --> |url=http://www.aolradioblog.com/features/top-jennifer-lopez-songs |title=Top 10 Jennifer Lopez Songs |publisher=AOL Radio Blog |date=May 9, 2012 |accessdate=2012-07-24}}</ref><ref name="top40about">{{cite web|author=Bill Lamb|url=http://top40.about.com/od/jenniferlopez/tp/top-10-jennifer-lopez-songs.htm|title=Jennifer Lopez Songs|publisher=about.com|accessdate=2012-07-24}}</ref> It received a heavy amount of airplay on the [[MTV Network]].<ref>{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=lfaqc1ByPg4C&pg=PA146&dq=jennifer+lopez+if+you+had+my+love&hl=en&sa=X&ei=3OkDUOnnKIiyiQfqpoDiBg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=jennifer%20lopez%20if%20you%20had%20my%20love&f=false |title=Latina/o Stars in U.S. Eyes: The Making and Meanings of Film and Tv Stardom – Mary Beltrán – Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com.au |date=July 13, 2009 |accessdate=2012-07-24}}</ref> A writer from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' wrote that Lopez "isn't too far behind Ricky Martin as the leading light of Latin Music in Asia"—and that the song had skyrocketed Lopez from an unknown to superstar status internationally, reaching music markets as diverse as India and the Philippines. Jeff Selamutu, a programming manager from [[Channel V]], said that "Up to now, it's only been [[Janet Jackson]] and [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]." Selamutu said that people were "enjoying her hot, sexy dancing on the video [for If You Had My Love]."<ref>{{cite book|title=Billboard Magazine|publisher=[[Nielsen Business Media, Inc.]]|url=http://books.google.com/?id=mAgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA54-IA2&dq=jennifer+lopez+if+you+had+my+love#v=onepage&q&f=false|accessdate=17-7-12|date=August 7, 1999}}</ref> The music video for "Waiting for Tonight" has been considered her best.<ref>{{cite web|last=Stack|first=Tim|title=Jennifer Lopez: 'Waiting for Tonight' was awesome...but it might be time to stop singing|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2009/11/23/jennifer-lopez-waiting-for-tonight-was-amazing-but-its-time-to-stop-singing/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=10-3-2012|date=23-11-09}}</ref> The song was used frequently as a celebratory anthem for the dawn of the new millenium. The music video was well-known for featuring a [[Y2K]] dance party.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/od/jenniferlopez/tp/top-10-jennifer-lopez-songs.htm |title=Jennifer Lopez Songs – The Top 10 Best Jennifer Lopez Songs |publisher=Top40.about.com |date=August 1, 2012 |accessdate=2012-08-05}}</ref> 

Lopez's video for "Jenny from the Block" remains her most controversial to date; it starred her then-fiancé [[Ben Affleck]] and included several racy scenes of her. Two years later, Lopez tried to have it pulled from television and ban it from airing.<ref>{{cite web|author=October 10, 2004 7:05:03 AM UTC |url=http://www.teenmusic.com/2004/10/10/j-los-video-block |title=J.Lo's video 'Block' |publisher=TeenMusic.com |date=October 10, 2004 |accessdate=2012-05-05}}</ref> The music video for "I'm Glad" was described as one of he more "complicated" videos. It recreated scenes from a 1983 film ''[[Flashdance]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/jenniferlopez/articles/story/5936040/lopez_sued_over_im_glad |title=Lopez Sued Over "I'm Glad" |accessdate=2008-08-16 |last=Devenish |first=Colin |date=November 14, 2003 |work=Rolling Stone}}</ref>
In the music video for "Get Right" directed by [[Francis Lawrence]], Lopez sports several different characters.<ref name="Rebirth booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=Rebirth (Dual Disc Edition) |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2005 |format=Booklet |publisher=Epic Records, a division of Sony Music Entertainment |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> The music video for "Do It Well" directed by [[David LaChapelle]] was set in an [[sadomasochism|S&M]] [[nightclub]] on Union Street.<ref name=guardianvideo>{{cite news|last=Pickard|first=Anna|title=Jennifer Lopez - Do It Well &#124; Culture &#124; guardian.co.uk|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2007/oct/03/popandrock|accessdate=2012-04-29|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=October 3, 2007}}</ref> "On the Floor" was praised for it's sex appeal which was compared to a previous video from almost a decade earlier, "I'm Gonna Be Alright" (2002).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.express.co.uk/posts/view/232698/Jennifer-Lopez-loses-her-curves-in-new-hit-On-the-Floor- |title=Jennifer Lopez Loses Her Curves in New Hit 'On the Floor' |work=The [[Daily Express]] |publisher=Northern and Shell Media Publications |date=March 5, 2011 |accessdate=2011-03-06}}</ref> Matthew Perpetua from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' said it was "classic Lopez tweaked for 2011."<ref>{{cite web|author=Matthew Perpetua |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/culture/blogs/rolling-stone-video-blog/jennifer-lopez-introduces-herself-to-a-new-j-lo-ration-with-on-the-floor-video-20110304#ixzz1pW7oJnmm |title=Jennifer Lopez Introduces Herself To a 'New J.Lo-Ration' With 'On the Floor' Video &#124; Matthew Perpetua |work=Rolling Stone |accessdate=2012-03-21}}</ref> The music video for "Dance Again" also became one of her most controversial. It featured Lopez's real-life boyfriend, Casper Smart. John Mitchell from [[MTV News]] looked back on Lopez's previous videos, saying that she had a "history" of flaunting her men in videos.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mitchell |first=John |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1682676/jennifer-lopez-dance-again-boyfriend-videos.jhtml |title=Jennifer Lopez Has History Of Flaunting Her Men In Videos – Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV |date=April 6, 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-14}}</ref> Throughout her music videos, she has worked with several directors and choreographers, including working with [[Paul Hunter (director)|Paul Hunter]], [[Francis Lawrence]] and [[Dave Meyers (director)|Dave Meyers]] several times.<ref name="Rebirth booklet" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2011/08/21/jennifer-lopez-dances-in-the-streets-in-papi-video/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Dances in the Streets in "Papi" Video |work=[[Rap-Up]] |date=October 18, 2010 |accessdate=2011-08-21}}</ref><ref name="Reel booklet">{{Cite album-notes |title=The Reel Me |artist=Jennifer Lopez |year=2003 |format=Booklet |publisher=Epic Records, a division of Sony Music Entertainment |location=New York City, NY}}</ref> She is considered a [[sex symbol]] through her music videos.<ref>{{cite news|last=Galkin |first=Alexandra |url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-03-04/entertainment/28673747_1_music-video-louboutins-floor |title=Jennifer Lopez's 'On the Floor' music video premieres on 'American Idol' – New York Daily News |publisher=Articles.nydailynews.com |date=March 4, 2011 |accessdate=2012-03-17}}</ref>

== Celebrity status and image ==
{{Quote box|width=350px|align=right|quote="She's a rarity. One of the few Hollywood stars you can actually admire. And when you meet her she's just as gorgeous, just as likeable, as she is on screen. I'm talking about J-Lo. Or for the uninitiated, Jennifer Lopez, a showbiz phenomenon who's up there with Madonna [...] she's been in more than 25 movies with leading men like [[George Clooney]], [[Robert Redford]] and [[Jack Nicholson]]. And, she's a merchandising marvel."|source=— [[Ray Martin (television presenter)|Ray Martin]] of ''[[60 minutes]]''<ref>{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Ray|title=J-Lo|url=http://sixtyminutes.ninemsn.com.au/stories/raymartin/304846/j-lo|accessdate=2012-02-28|date=October 11, 2007}}</ref>
}}

Lopez has been said to have epitomized the definition of America's sweetheart, having crept into millions of homes with her music, movies, accessories and clothing lines.<ref name=ballet /> Lopez is described as the most influential Hispanic performer in the United States; she became the first Latin actress or singer to be so commercially successful in the limelight.<ref name=rantrack /><ref name="hhh" /> [[Nobel Prize]] recipient [[José Ramos-Horta]] called Lopez a remarkable woman and true inspiration after seeing her work on the film ''Bordertown''.<ref name="hhh" /> Cindy Pearlman from ''[[The Record (Waterloo Region)|The Record]]'' said that Lopez is responsible for welcoming a "Latina presence to a film industry"; considering that for much of its history it had been a whites-only preserve.<ref name=therecord>{{cite news|last=Pearlman|first=Cindy|title=For the record; Very hot and ambitious actress Jennifer Lopez has music on her mind|accessdate=2012-02-15|newspaper=[[The Record (Waterloo Region)|The Record]]|date=August 14, 1999|location=Kitchener, Ontario}}</ref> In ''Icons of American Popular Culture'' (2009), author Robert C. Cotrell described Lopez as being a Latina [[Oprah Winfrey]] and the embodiment of the American dream, "Boasting a far more authentic rags-to-riches tale". Cotrell stated that she is a "multidimensional artist who had turned into a financial powerhouse [...] In a largely singular fashion, Lopez had demonstrated that a Latina could remain on the Hollywood "A" list, to be a top recording artist, and operate as a major player in the corporate world, with her perfumes alone pulling over $500 million annually."<ref name="hhh">{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com/?id=ZXRcV6k0F9sC&pg=PA221&lpg=PA221&dq=Jennifer+Lopez+spanish+icon#v=onepage&q=Jennifer%20Lopez%20spanish%20icon&f=false |title=Icons of American Popular Culture: From P.T.Barnum to Jennifer Lopez – Robert C. Cottrell |publisher=Google Books |date= September 1, 2009|accessdate=2012-03-10|isbn=978-0-7656-2299-0}}</ref>

[[File:Wax Jennifer Lopez.jpg|thumb|200px|left]]

Lopez has changed her personal appearance multiple times, scoring several different hairstyles over the years.<ref name="fashionthestyle">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez: 12 Years' Beautiful Transmutation|url=http://www.fashionthestyle.com/a/people_parties/Celebs_Street_Style/2011/0829/302.html|publisher=Fashionthestyle.com|accessdate=2012-01-10|author=Johnphy|date=August 29, 2011}}</ref> She has been described as a [[sex symbol]] and having a reputation as "one of the most desirable women on the planet."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2016603/Jennifer-Lopez-divorce-Controlling-Marc-Anthony-hated-J-Lo-sex-symbol.html |title=Jennifer Lopez divorce: Controlling Marc Anthony 'hated J-Lo being a sex symbol' &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=July 20, 2011 |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref> She has also been described as a "[[siren]]" and "Bronx Barbie".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popcrush.com/jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-today-show-interview/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Discusses Working With Marc Anthony on ‘Today’ |publisher=Popcrush.com |date=January 30, 2012 |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Us Weekly&nbsp;–&nbsp;Wed, Apr 18, 2012 12:50 PM PDT |url=http://tv.yahoo.com/news/jennifer-lopezs-stylist-shes-bronx-barbie-195005543.html |title=Jennifer Lopez's Stylist: She's "Bronx Barbie" – Yahoo! TV |publisher=Tv.yahoo.com |date=April 18, 2012 |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref> Despite her fashion, which Lauren Savage of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' noted was "stunning" and "albeit scantily-clad", Lopez has stated: "I know how to fight! [...] I can take a lot of punches and still keep going. I've been trained like a boxer to go 15 rounds."<ref>{{cite web|last=Savage|first=Lauren|title=J.Lo Plays Gender-Bending Boxer for V Magazine Cover|url=http://www.billboard.com/column/the-hook/j-lo-plays-gender-bending-boxer-for-v-magazine-1006314952.story#IoDpB0xUgBGEUlYB.99|work=[[Billboard (magazine){{!}}Billboard]]|accessdate=2012-08-20|date=February 29, 2012}}</ref> Lopez is noted in the media for her curvaceous figure, in particular her [[buttocks]], and was called "original doyenne of derriere" by Katherine Ormerod of ''[[Grazia]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Katherine Ormerod |url=http://www.graziadaily.co.uk/fashion/archive/2012/04/30/the-rise-of-the-super-bum--kim-kardashian--nikki-minaj---jlo-show-how-to-dress-y.htm |title=The Rise of the Super Bum: Kim Kardashian, Nicki Minaj & Jennifer Lopez Show How to Dress Your Booty &#124; Grazia Fashion |publisher=Graziadaily.co.uk |date=April 30, 2012 |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Sarah Bull |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2159645/Jennifer-Lopez-shows-famous-curves-sheer-diamante-catsuit.html |title=Jennifer Lopez shows off her famous curves in a sheer diamante catsuit &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=June 15, 2012 |accessdate=2012-07-07}}</ref> In a survey by [[Nutrisystem|Nutrisystem Diet Index]], it was revealed that most American females would have her legs and butt.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez's butt, Vin Diesel's arms favoured by US women, men|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Jennifer+Lopez's+butt,+Vin+Diesel's+arms+favoured+by+US+women,+men.-a0257359190|publisher=Al Bawaba (Middle East) Ltd. (thefreelibrary.com)|accessdate=2012-02-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=ANI|title=Jennifer Lopez's butt, Vin Diesel's arms favoured by US women, men|url=http://in.news.yahoo.com/jennifer-lopezs-butt-vin-diesels-arms-favoured-us-101512607.html|publisher=[[Yahoo]] (in.news.yahoo.com)|accessdate=2012-02-04|date=May 26, 2011}}</ref> Lopez has been criticized by the [[animal rights]] organization [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals]] for her use of fur in her fashion lines.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peta.org/b/thepetafiles/archive/2011/08/04/how-low-will-j_2d00_lo-go_3f00_.aspx |title=PETA: How Low Will J-Lo Go? |publisher=PETA.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-03}}</ref> Celebrities such as [[Pink (singer)|Pink]] and [[Pamela Anderson]] also have criticized her for this, too.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecelebrityblog.com/2005/09/pink-has-slammed-jennifer-lopez-and-beyonce-for-wearing-fur/ |title=Pink has slammed Jennifer Lopez and Beyonce for wearing fur |date= |accessdate=2012-08-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news-article/anderson-blasts-jlo-and-diddy-over-fur-coats |title=Pamela Anderson – Anderson Blasts J.Lo And Diddy Over Fur Coats |date= |accessdate=2012-08-04}}</ref> Lopez has changed her personal appearance multiple times, sporting numerous different hairstyles over the years.<ref name="fashionthestyle"/> In November 1998, Lopez was named "Sexiest Woman of the Year" by [[Details (magazine)|''Details'' magazine]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Halza|first=George Halza|title=Jennifer Lopez named sexiest woman of the year|accessdate=2012-02-22|newspaper=[[Reading Eagle]]|date=November 16, 1998|page=5|format=Newspaper}}</ref> Lopez appeared on ''[[FHM]]''{{'}}s "100 Sexiest Women" list multiple times, leading the list for two consecutive years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/jennifer-lopez |title=''FHM'' – Jennifer Lopez |publisher=Fhm.com |accessdate=2012-03-10}}</ref> In 2011, Lopez was first on ''People'' magazine's list of "[[People Magazine's 100 Most Beautiful People|100 Most Beautiful People]]".<ref>{{cite web|last=Jordan|first=Julie|title=Jennifer Lopez: Being Beautiful Is 'Part of My Job'|url=http://www.people.com/people/package/article/0,,20360857_20481259,00.html|publisher=(people.com)|accessdate=2012-01-29|date=April 13, 2011}}</ref>

American record producer [[Randy Jackson]] stated that although she doesn't have the "biggest voice in the world", "she can sing. It's the (complete) package [...]".<ref>{{cite web|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|title='Idol' Judge Randy Jackson Gives Jennifer Lopez's Singing a '7'|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/idol-judge-randy-jackson-gives-jennifer-1004139399.story#/news/idol-judge-randy-jackson-gives-jennifer-1004139399.story|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=2012-02-12}}</ref> Daniel Chang from ''[[The Spectator]]'' said that: "Lopez will achieve more success as an actress than she will as a singer. Which is to say, Lopez can sing, but there are better introductions to Latin and R&B music out there."<ref>{{cite web|last=Chang|first=Daniel|title=Six appeal Jennifer Lopez releases her first CD|work=The Spectator |date=June 1, 1999}}</ref> In 2007, ''The York Press'' said that Lopez's Spanish album ''Como Ama Una Mujer'' "proved that she is a major musical force" and commented that Lopez's voice had a greater depth and that: "So far into her career, Lopez is at last making great records [...] Her material is also far stronger."<ref name=compare>{{cite web|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/1818825.m5ec/?from=ec&to=1818825&l=britney_spears_blackout_jive_jennifer_lopez_brave_epic_ |title=Britney Spears, Blackout (Jive) ****; Jennifer Lopez, Brave (Epic) **** (From York Press) |publisher=Yorkpress.co.uk |date=November 8, 2007 |accessdate=2012-10-20}}</ref> ''[[The Press (York)|The York Press]]'' also complimented Lopez for not needing as much "digital enhancement" on her voice compared to singers like [[Britney Spears]].<ref name=compare /> A writer from ''[[The Baltimore Sun|The Sun]]'' said ''On the 6'' "makes it clear she can sing. [Jennifer] Lopez has no trouble handling the material presented to her [...] No doubt about it, as a singer, Lopez has a lot of talent and stylistic range. Instead, she ends up doing impressions, singing as other, more distinctive, performers might have. So when producer [[Sean Combs]] fabricates a lush, [[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis]]-type groove, she responds by offering her best Janet Jackson imitation". He went on to compliment her duet, "No Me Ames", with Anthony and said: "It isn't as if Lopez is merely a chameleon, without a sound to call her own"<ref>{{cite news|title=Actress Jennifer Lopez can sing, but it isn't enough|accessdate=2012-02-12|newspaper=[[The Baltimore Sun|The Sun]]|date=June 3, 1999|location=Baltimore}}</ref> Tom Sinclair of ''Entertainment Weekly'' commented on Lopez's vocals stating that: "There's no way to know if Jennifer Lopez's voice is mechanically altered or not, but on the recorded evidence of her sophomore album, ''J.Lo'', her singing seems to be in key".<ref name="Entertainment Weekly February 5, 2001">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,97933~4~0~jenniferlopezjlo,00.html|title=J.Lo – Music Review |last=Sinclair|first=Tom|date=February 5, 2001|work=Entertainment Weekly|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=2010-04-16}}</ref>

== Legacy ==
{{see also|List of accolades received by Jennifer Lopez}}

Since the beginning of her career, Lopez has been honored with numerous awards and recognition. In 1998, Lopez received a [[Golden Globe]] nomination for her role in ''Selena''. She has been present on ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'''s Annual Actress Salary List three times consecutively from 2002–04.<ref name="highest">[http://web.archive.org/web/20070511172332/http://www.itsasurvey.com/artman2/publish/entertainment/Nicole_Kidman_Tops_The_Hollywood_Reporter_s_Annual_Actress_Salary_List_Reese_Witherspoon_Comes_in_at_No_2.shtml Nicole Kidman Tops The Hollywood Reporter's Annual Actress Salary List.] (November 30, 2006). ItsaSurvey.com. Retrieved 2007-05-05.</ref> She remains the only Latin actress to accomplish this.<ref name="highest" /> Lopez was paid over $2&nbsp;million for her role in the critically acclaimed film ''[[Out of Sight]]'', becoming the highest-paid Latin actress.<ref name="MSNbio">{{cite web|url=http://movies.msn.com/celebrities/celebrity-biography/jennifer-lopez/ |title=Jennifer Lopez:Biography |publisher=Movies.msn.com |accessdate=2011-08-06}}</ref><ref name="Jennifer Lopez pics">{{cite web |url=http://www.askmen.com/women/singer/3c_jennifer_lopez.html |title=Jennifer Lopez pics |accessdate=2007-01-13 |work=[[AskMen.com]]}}</ref><ref name="nydailynews1998"/> Having sold over 70 million units worldwide, she is recognized as one of the [[List of best-selling music artists|best selling musical artists]] in the history of [[contemporary music]].<ref name="70millionrecords">{{cite web|author=June 25, 2012&nbsp; |url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2012/06/jennifer-lopez-to-issue-greatest-hits-package.html |title=Jennifer Lopez to issue greatest-hits package - latimes.com |publisher=Latimesblogs.latimes.com |date=June 25, 2012 |accessdate=2012-07-10|page=m|unused_data=&nbsp;12:48}}</ref> Numerous albums and songs of hers have been certified by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]].<ref name="riaa">{{cite web |url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?artist=Lopez,_Jennifer |title = RIAA – Gold & Platinum: Jennifer Lopez |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |accessdate=2011-08-10}}</ref> In December 2009, ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' ranked Lopez as the 27th Artist of the 2000s decade.<ref name=decadee>http://www.billboard.com/#/charts-decade-end/artists-of-the-decade?year=2009&begin=21&order=position</ref> At the 2010 [[World Music Awards]], Lopez was honored the legend award for Outstanding Contribution to the Arts.<ref>{{cite web|author=Emily Sheridan |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1279581/World-Music-Awards-Jennifer-Lopez-shows-wild-animal-print-dresses.html |title=World Music Awards: Jennifer Lopez shows her wild side in two animal-print dresses &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=May 19, 2010 |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref> Additionally, she has garnered six [[ALMA Awards]], three [[American Music Awards]], ten [[Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]], eight [[Teen Choice Awards]], six [[MTV Awards]] and two World Music Awards, among several others. In 2012, she was ranked 16th on [[VH1]]'s list of "100 Greatest Women In Music."<ref>{{cite web|last=Graham|first=Mark|title=VH1's 100 Greatest Women In Music (COMPLETE LIST)|url=http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2012-02-13/vh1s-100-greatest-women-in-music-complete-list/|publisher=[[VH1]]|accessdate=2012-02-29|date=February 13, 2012}}</ref> Lopez's return to the musical spotlight in 2011 was considered the best comeback of the year, and among the greatest comebacks ever.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best of 2011: Jennifer Lopez's Sizzling Comeback|url=http://omg.yahoo.com/news/best-2011-jennifer-lopezs-sizzling-comeback-215952021.html|publisher=(omg.yahoo.com)|accessdate=2012-02-05|date=December 24, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Best of 2011: Jennifer Lopez's Sizzling Comeback|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/best-of-2011-jennifer-lopezs-sizzling-comeback-20112412|work=[[Us Magazine]]|publisher=(usmagazine.com)|accessdate=2012-02-05|date=December 24, 2011}}</ref><ref name=comeback /> The music video for "On the Floor" was lauded by critics, and became [[YouTube]]'s highest-viewed video for the year; while also becoming the second most viewed video of all time, and most-viewed by a female.<ref>{{cite web|last=Goerge|first=Kat|title=Rebecca Black's "Friday" And Jennifer Lopez And Pitbull's "On The Floor" Rule YouTube In 2011|url=http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2011-12-21/rebecca-blacks-friday-and-jennifer-lopez-and-pitbulls-on-the-floor-rule-youtube-in-2011/|publisher=[[VH1]]|accessdate=2012-02-29|date=December 21, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bhatt|first=Neha|title=Jennifer Lopez is the Queen of Youtube!|url=http://www.desihits.com/news/view/jennifer-lopez-is-the-queen-of-youtube-20111116|publisher=desihits.com|accessdate=2012-02-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hilton|first=Perez|title=Jennifer Lopez Queen Of YouTube!|url=http://perezhilton.com/2011-11-14-jennifer-lopez-on-the-floor-most-watched-youtube-video-by-female-artist|publisher=[[Perez Hilton]]|accessdate=2012-02-29}}</ref> ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' named her the "World's Greatest Comeback Act" of the decade; a ranking from an accuracast—a digital search that analyzed over a billion [[Google]] searches since 2004.<ref name=comeback>{{cite news|last=Kennedy|first=Gerrick D.|title=Jennifer Lopez named 'world's greatest musical comeback act' – seriously|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2011/12/jennifer-lopez-named-worlds-greatest-musical-comeback-act-seriously.html|work=Los Angeles Times|publisher=(latimesblogs.latimes.com)|accessdate=2012-01-29|date=December 13, 2011}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Reader's Poll also named her the best comeback of the year.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|title=Britney Spears, Adele Rule Billboard.com's Readers Poll 2011|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/britney-spears-adele-rule-billboard-com-1005683362.story#/news/britney-spears-adele-rule-billboard-com-1005683362.story|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] (billboard.com)|accessdate=2012-01-29|location=New York|date=December 15, 2011}}</ref> Also in 2011, she was the 3rd most-searched artist on the internet and 5th most searched human.<ref>{{cite web|author=Photos: Getty Images |url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2011/11/29/the-10-most-searched-people-of-2011-%E2%80%94-justin-bieber-beats-kim-kardashian-list/ |title=10 Most Searched People of 2011 — Justin Bieber Bumps Kim Kardashian [LIST&#93; &#124; Ryan Seacrest - The official entertainment news site of American Idol host and American Top 40 on air radio personality! |publisher=Ryan Seacrest |date=November 29, 2011 |accessdate=2012-04-09}}</ref> Lopez's album ''J to tha L-O! The Remixes'' (2002) is the first number one remix album on the ''Billboard'' 200.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.famousqt.com/profile.asp?celeb=38 |title=Jennifer Lopez Biography Page |accessdate=2006-09-06 |work=FamoustQt.com}}</ref> It appeared in the 2004 ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as the most successful remix album.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3186761.stm |title=Diaz tops actress pay list |accessdate=2009-04-18 |date=August 27, 2004 |work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref> 

''[[Us Weekly]]'' named her Style Icon of the 2000s decade.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez: Us' Style Icon of the Decade|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-style/pictures/jlo-through-the-years-2010204/7767|publisher=[[Us Weekly Magazine]]|accessdate=2012-01-10}}</ref> Lopez's most memorable Fashion moment in her career was the [[Green Versace "jungle" dress of Jennifer Lopez|Green Versace "Jungle Dress"]] that she wore at the [[42nd Grammy Awards]] In 2000.<ref name="PhillipsReay2002">{{cite book|editor1-last=Phillips|editor-first=Kim M.|editor2-last=Reay|editor2-first=Barry|title=Sexualities in history: a reader|chapter-url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Cz3bPMw_7h4C&pg=PA407|last=Barrera|first=Magdalena|chapter=Hottentot 2000: ''Jennifer Lopez and Her Butt''|accessdate=2011-05-16|year=2002|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-415-92935-6|page=407}}</ref> A poll by [[Debenhams]], published in the ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'', voted it the fifth most iconic dress of all time.<ref name="Telegraph08">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/3167702/Liz-Hurley-safety-pin-dress-voted-the-greatest-dress.html|author=Urmee Khan|title=Liz Hurley 'safety pin' dress voted the greatest dress |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=October 9, 2008|accessdate=2011-05-01|separator=,|location=London}}</ref> For her Fashion sense, Lopez has earned several awards including a VH1 Award and Vogue Fashion Award in 1999 for "Most Fashionable Female Artist", achieving multiple other awards since for outstanding achievements and recognition.  ''[[People en Español]]'' listed her atop their "100 Most Influential Hispanics" list on their February 2007 addition.<ref name=leading1>{{cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/peopleNews/idUSN0417833620070105|title=J.Lo tops list of most influential Hispanics|accessdate=2007-02-12|agency=Reuters |date=January 4, 2007}}</ref> In May 2012, ''[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]'' placed Lopez first on the [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list, naming her the most powerful celebrity for the past year, having earned $52 million in the past year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-05-17/lopez-tops-forbes-most-powerful-list/4016018 |title=Lopez tops Forbes most powerful list – ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation) |publisher=Abc.net.au |date=May 17, 2012 |accessdate=2012-05-24}}</ref> Dorothy Pomerantz of ''Forbes'' said that it was due to her role as judge on ''American Idol'', endorsement deals and her much publicized personal life.<ref>{{cite news|author=Dorothy Pomerantz |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/05/16/jennifer-lopez-tops-celebrity-100-list/ |title=J.Lo's Stunning Career Reincarnation Puts Her No. 1 On The Celebrity 100 |publisher=Forbes |date=April 18, 2012 |accessdate=2012-05-24}}</ref> 

Lopez has received much praise over the course of her career, with several entertainers having acknowledged her as an influence. She has influenced music artists such as [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/fergie-mn0000725395/related|title=Fergie – Similar Artists, Influenced By, Followers|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=2012-07-24}}</ref> [[Thalía]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/thal%C3%ADa-mn0000751201/related |title=Thalía – Similar Artists, Influenced By, Followers |publisher=AllMusic |accessdate=2012-07-24}}</ref> and [[Kat DeLuna]].<ref name="DeLuna">{{cite news|first=Gatecrasher|title=J.Lo's new song sounds suspiciously like one from Hispanic hottie Kat DeLuna|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-01-19/gossip/27087962_1_jlo-kat-deluna-similarities|work=New York Daily News|publisher=(articles.nydailynews.com)|accessdate=2012-02-04|date=January 19, 2011}}</ref> [[Kerry Washington]] has cited Lopez as the reason for her career, she explained: "I grew up blocks away from Jennifer Lopez. She and I went to the same Boys & Girls Club. She was like the dancer who made it big and moved to Hollywood. I don't know if I would've taken a risk in my career if it weren't for [Jennifer]."<ref>{{cite web|title=Kerry Washington: Lopez inspired me|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/news/kerry-washington-lopez-inspired-me-16111987.html|publisher=(belfasttelegraph.co.uk)|accessdate=2012-02-04|date=February 1, 2012}}</ref> DeLuna has stated: "Jennifer helped pave the way for Latinas like myself. I love her."<ref name="DeLuna"/> [[Britney Spears]] stated: "Jennifer Lopez is my idol – she's so beautiful and even though she's gotten older, she hasn't aged at all. She looks more amazing than ever and I really admire and respect that."<ref>{{cite web|title=Britney Spears – Britney Spears Admires Jennifer Lopez|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/britney-spears-admires-jennifer-lopez_1266386|work=Contact Music|publisher=(contactmusic.com)|accessdate=2012-02-04|date=November 30, 2011}}</ref> [[Raquel Castro]]—her co-star from the film ''[[Jersey Girl (2004 film)|Jersey Girl]]'' (2004)—said that she has a strong bond with Lopez, who was her main role model for her career.<ref name=raq /> Castro said: "Jennifer Lopez has been my role model from the start. I wore out my VCR tape of the movie ''Selena'', probably watching it a million times; when I found out I had been chosen to play her daughter in a feature-ﬁlm, OMG I was screaming like crazy."<ref name=raq>{{cite web|title=Raquel Castro Biography|url=http://raquelcastro.com/Bio.html|publisher=(raquelcastro.com)|accessdate=2012-02-04}}</ref> [[Jessica Mauboy]] has said stated that she is a big fan of Lopez.<ref name="claire">{{cite web|url=http://au.lifestyle.yahoo.com/marie-claire/features/society-celeb/article/-/8345358/interview-jessica-mauboy/ |first=Anna|last=Tsekouras|title=Interview: Jessica Mauboy |work=Marie Claire |publisher=Yahoo!7 |date=November 18, 2010|accessdate=2010-12-12}}</ref> [[Mike Doughty|Michael Doughty]] said that Lopez was a key inspiration for reviving his music career as a solo artist after leaving his band, [[Soul Coughing]]. He explained: "One of the key moments was seeing a Jennifer Lopez video [...] She's a year older than me and she's in this video and she's in the Bronx and going out clubbing and going to the beauty salon. I'd thought, well I'm 29, my life's over, I'm elderly. And I looked at her and thought, she's 30, how is she walking? [...] the revelation came watching a Jennifer Lopez video."<ref>{{cite web|last=Letkemman|first=Jessica|title=Mike Doughty Opens 'Book of Drugs,' Says J.Lo & Music Thieves Saved His Life|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/news/mike-doughty-opens-book-of-drugs-says-j-1005628152.story|work=Billboard |accessdate=2012-02-26|location=New York|date=December 7, 2011}}</ref> [[Nicki Minaj]] stated: "I love J-Lo. I love what she's done for pop culture I have nothing but respect for her."<ref>{{cite news|author=3 DAYS |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-nicki-minaj-jennifer-lopez-306043 |title=Nicki Minaj-Jennifer Lopez Feud Sparked on 'American Idol' Stage |publisher=Hollywood Reporter |date=March 25, 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref> [[Selena Gomez]] stated that seeing Lopez's performance in the film ''[[Selena (film)|Selena]]'' was a "life-changing moment." Gomez talked about emulating Lopez’s attire that she wore in the film during the same interview with [[Elle Magazine]].<ref name=SelenaGomez>{{cite news| url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/06/08/selena-gomez-gets-racy-in-elle-photoshoot/ | work=Fox News | title=Selena Gomez Gets Racy in ‘Elle' Photoshoot | date=June 8, 2012}}</ref> [[Kelly Rowland]] and [[Kim Kardashian]] have credited her as their major style icon and inspiration.<ref name="styleicons">{{cite web|url=http://photos.essence.com/galleries/kelly_rowland__style_icons#!881733|title=Kelly Rowland: Style Icons|work=Essence|publisher=Time Inc|accessdate=2012-05-12}}</ref><ref name="kimj">{{cite web|last=Coughlan|first=Maggie|title=Kim Kardashian Considers Jennifer Lopez a Style Icon|url=http://www.popeater.com/2011/02/15/kim-kardashian-qvc-fashion-week/|publisher=PopEater|accessdate=2012-01-10|date=February 15, 2011}}</ref>

